==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homonymy
<hw>Ho*mon"y*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>homonymie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sameness of name or
designation; identity in relations.</def> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Homonymy</qex> may be as well in place as in persons.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sameness of name or designation of things or persons
which are different; ambiguity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homoorgan</ent>⟦br⟧
